channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: 2 Americans among missing passengers from sunken superyacht
item.description: Two Americans are among those still missing after a superyacht sank off the coast of Sicily on Monday, ABC News has confirmed.

item.title: ‘I lost so much’: California Home Depot fired 70-year-old woman who processed $5K in fraudulent transactions — now she’s suing
The president is coming to town for vacation. Get ready.
item.description: President Biden is vacationing this week in Santa Ynez, California. Presidential vacations can cause some headaches.

item.title: Illinois bans corporal punishment in all schools
item.description: Illinois will soon become just the fifth state in the nation to prohibit corporal punishment in all schools

item.title: She says Israeli military killed her husband and daughter. Then soldiers brought her to an Israeli hospital
DNC Day 2: Here's what to expect from the second day of the Democratic convention
item.description: Democrats from across the country are returning for Day 2 of the Democratic National Convention as the party continues to rally around its new ticket.

item.title: 'Right thing to do': George Santos addresses pleading guilty to federal charges
item.description: Former Rep. George Santos, R-N.Y., on Monday pleaded guilty to wire fraud and aggravated identity theft.

item.title: Experts sound alarm after finding invasive species capable of wiping out ecosystem in major US river: 'The ramifications cannot be underestimated or overstated'
Day 2 of DNC expected to bring more protests, demonstrations
item.description: Thousands marched in a show of solidarity with Palestine and calling for an end to U.S. funding to Israel.

item.title: Detroit police search for arsonist after explosion destroys cars
item.description: The Detroit Police Department is seeking public help in their search for an arson suspect who burned four vehicles and damaged two others late last week.

item.title: Gwen Walz reveals she underwent a different treatment, not IVF, in new details about fertility struggles
World's oldest person, U.S.-born Spanish woman, dies at 117, family says
item.description: Spain's Maria Branyas Morera, the world's oldest living person, who was born in the U.S. and lived through two world wars, the Spanish Civil War and the COVID pandemic, has died at 117, her family said Tuesday.

item.title: Over 600 pounds of methamphetamine found inside celery shipment
item.description: More than 600 pounds of methamphetamine have been found concealed within a shipment of celery in California, officials said.

item.title: A German court upholds the conviction of a former secretary at a Nazi concentration camp, age 99
Disney changes course on wrongful death lawsuit
item.description: Disney has now dropped its effort to get a wrongful death lawsuit dismissed over the fine print in it's Disney+ streaming app. The company had previously said its terms include an arbitration clause.
